      <p>Every estimator has a shelf of books that promise the "perfect" formula for profit. From the industry-standard RSMeans manuals to Peterson’s "bibles" on quantity takeoff, these resources provide a rock-solid foundation for the theory of construction estimating. But in 2025, theory is hitting a ceiling.</p>

